adjective.description: Of or characteristic of the reigns of the British Kings George I–IV (1714–1830).
Of or characteristic of the reigns of the British Kings George V and VI (1910–52).

noun.description: A native or inhabitant of the country Georgia, or a person of Georgian descent.
The South Caucasian (or Kartvelian) language, having its own alphabet, that is the official language of Georgia.
